City Lodge, Distell Group, Hyprop Investments: South African Stock Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-02-16T06:27:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/city-lodge-distell-group-hyprop-investments-south-african-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South
Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and
prices are from yesterday’s close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined
33.78, or 0.1 percent, to 33,060.28 in Johannesburg.    BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ): The world’s largest mining
company said fiscal first-half net income increased to $10.5
billion, from $6.1 billion a year earlier.  BHP Billiton  dropped
1.66 rand, or 0.6 percent, to 295.35 rand.    City Lodge Hotels Ltd . (CLH SJ): The hotel operator
releases first-half earnings for the period through December.
City Lodge fell 1.15 rand, or 1.6 percent, to 69.25 rand.    Distell Group Ltd . (DST SJ): South Africa’s biggest wine
and liquor maker releases first-half earnings for the period
through December. The share decreased 25 cents, or 0.3 percent,
to 77.25 rand.    Hyprop Investments Ltd . (HYP SJ): The real-estate investor
said because of differences of opinion with the board on
operational issues, Mike Rodel will step down from his position
as chief executive officer after the annual earnings
presentation in March. The stock was unchanged at 54.85 rand.    Liberty Holdings Ltd . (LBH SJ): The insurer owned by
Standard Bank Group Ltd., South Africa’s largest lender, said it
will post earnings per share of between 8.90 rand and 9.80 rand
for the year through December. Liberty Holdings rose 59 cents,
or 0.8 percent, to 74.64 rand.  SacOil Holdings Ltd. (SCL SJ): The oil and natural gas
explorer said it is in advanced negotiations with energy company
Total SA for the latter to buy into SacOil’s Block 3 oil section
in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. The share gained 7
cents, or 4.1 percent, to 1.76 rand.    Santam Ltd . (SNT SJ): South Africa’s largest property and
casualty insurer said earnings per share jumped between 40
percent and 55 percent. Santam slipped 14 cents, or 0.1 percent,
to 126 rand.  WG Wearne Ltd. (WEA SJ): The concrete maker said it is
unspecified talks that may affect the value of its shares. The
stock declined 4 cents, or 18 percent, to 18 cents.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) declined 3.2 percent to
$26.60. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) gained 1.9 percent to
$45.91. BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) dropped 1.7 percent to $80.75.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) lost 0.9 percent to $4.55. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) jumped 1.8 percent to $16.16. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) added 1.4 percent to $10.89. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) dropped 1.1 percent to $29.05. Sappi Ltd.
(SPP US) rose 1.2 percent to $5.26. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) declined
1.4 percent to $51.18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
